All ready for marathon #44 tomorrow💕 I have to say this is the least trained I have ever been for a marathon. Work, being a single mom and life has been my priority these last few months.. I am here to run because I was given the gift of running again after having a broken hip and surgery. I am here because I love running…Trained or not.. I will show up and run the race, kinda like life these days. I will never give up. I am stubborn like that. Tomorrow I will run my race and think about how grateful I am. See you all at the finish line tomorrow❤️#marathoner #marathonmaniacs #teamaltra #thankful #grateful #cim @runcim262 #letsdothis

Marathon #44 is complete. I didn’t have the best race but that’s what I get for not training. I enjoyed the rolling hills until mile 10 then I was done with them😭 It started to get warm, I slowed down and decided I wasn’t going to kill myself. Am I a little bit disappointed? Yes. Is it my own fault for not training? Absolutely! The @cim marathon may be a one and done for me at least for a few years but that’s okay. I am looking forward to focusing on training for Boston 2023 after the holidays. Either way, it was a good day! I got to run!❤️ Cheers to marathon 44 and  my 9th marathon post broken hip and surgery💕 #marathoner #cim #marathonmaniacs #happy #tired #teamaltra @runcim262

It was a great year of running races!❤️ so many good times with good friends! I am a lucky girl🥰

I still haven’t ran since my marathon in Sacramento. I am not injured. I am trying to move my urgent care😭❤️ I have been working the last 9/10 days and still have a couple more to go. I would do anything for my amazing team and the children. Moving to a bigger space in the hospital means we get to see more pediatric patients❤️ And this is all about the children🏥💕I just have to say, I have never worked with such a wonderful team! I am such a lucky girl🥰 #pediatricnurse #registerednurse #seattlechildrenshospital

10 mile trail run this afternoon!! First run in 2 weeks!💕 I have been so busy with life and getting ready to move my urgent care, I haven’t had time to run since my last marathon 2 weeks ago. It felt so good to be on the trails and back in my happy place today! I have been a bit emotional this past week due to stress and mental exhaustion but also gratefulness. My boss made me take the day off today after being at work almost every day the last two weeks😭 I will be ready to go when we open in our new space tomorrow!!🏥🥰 #marathonrecovery #singlemom #pediaricnurse #registerednurse #marathoner #trails #trailrunning #trailrunner #optoutside #winter #teamaltra

We did it!!!🎉 Our urgent care officially opened in the new space today! We had one month to plan the move and get it done. We were told it would be impossible by several people. It literally took a village… working nonstop, so many meetings and spreadsheets.. It was an emotional roller coaster at times.. But I knew we would get it done❤️🏥 I have literally never worked with a better team in my 20 years of nursing. I truly love my work family🥰 #urgentcare #pediatricnurse #childrenshospital #move #teamwork #myworkfamily

Cheers to my Friday and one of the busiest months of my life… This month I ran a marathon in California, moved my Urgent Care to a new location in the hospital, planned and had a holiday party for my staff, onboarded two new travel nurses, interviewed three MA’s (by the end of next week), did 5 staff annual evaluations…and oh ya, Christmas! It’s FINALLY time to relax❤️ Also, 25 degrees outside doesn’t feel too bad in the hot tub😉😭#christmastime #cheers #relax #timetorelax #hottubtime #babyitscoldoutside #pediatricnurse #registerednurse #marathoner #singlemomlife

Marathon #46 is done…13 days after the @bostonmarathon. Today was a first, running with a broken hand and cast. I had already registered for the race before I broke my hand. I decided to do it…because why not… I like to do hard things.. The cast is kinda heavy and threw my stride off. I couldn’t tell if the race hard because of the cast and broken hand or tired legs from Boston. Either way another marathon is finished. Ans I placed 2nd in my division! I am pretty tired now.. So many hills were climbed today. But my heart is happy. I am grateful for each day I get to run❤️ Time for hot tub and food💕 @tcma_events #marathonmaniacs @marathonmaniacs #nuunlife #tcma #runtacoma #tiredlegshappyheart #grit #perseverance #nevergiveup

White River 50 Mile Trail Race..From climbing uphill at mile 37, first pic to the finish line, second pic. What a day Saturday was. When someone asked me why I do this race. I said because I want to be reminded that I can do hard things.. I don’t share too much about my personal life anymore but I feel like this race represents my life. The first half, was like the last 10 years of my life with the burnt trees and new growth, knowing even though things were destroyed or ended, new beautiful life is growing.. The second half reminded me of my current life… difficult and somewhat alone… but knowing there are great things to come like the finish line. My body is pretty beat up with blisters, cuts, abrasions and chaffing.. but I wouldn’t have it any other way. I did it! I completed the race.. and once again..I know I can do hard things❤️ #whiteriver50 #icandohardthings #ultrarunning #ultrarunner #trails #trailrunning #trailrunner #singlemomlife @rainshadowrunning
